Source class.","pos":[43948,44007]},{"content":"The change only affects apps that use EventListener to read EventSource data in process and that use null characters as delimiters.","pos":[44008,44139]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[44144,44154]},{"content":"EventSource data should be updated, if possible, to not use embedded null characters.","pos":[44155,44240]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[44245,44250]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[44251,44255]},{"content":"Version","pos":[44260,44267]},{"content":"4.5.1","pos":[44268,44273]},{"content":"Type","pos":[44278,44282]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[44283,44290]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[44295,44308]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[45102,45111]},{"content":"CD0046","pos":[45112,45118]},{"pos":[45159,45257],"content":"48: ObsoleteAttribute exports as both ObsoleteAttribute and DeprecatedAttribute in WinMD scenarios","linkify":"48: ObsoleteAttribute exports as both ObsoleteAttribute and DeprecatedAttribute in WinMD scenarios","nodes":[{"content":"48: ObsoleteAttribute exports as both ObsoleteAttribute and DeprecatedAttribute in WinMD scenarios","pos":[0,98]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[45278,45285]},{"content":"When you create a Windows Metadata library (.winmd file), the ObsoleteAttribute attribute is exported as both ObsoleteAttribute and Windows.Foundation.DeprecatedAttribute.","pos":[45286,45457]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[45462,45472]},{"content":"Recompilation of existing source code that uses the ObsoleteAttribute attribute may generate warnings when consuming that code from C++/CX or JavaScript.","pos":[45473,45626]},{"content":"We do not recommend applying both ObsoleteAttribute and Windows.Foundation.DeprecatedAttribute to code in managed assemblies; it may result in build warnings.","pos":[45639,45797]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[45802,45807]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[45808,45812]},{"content":"Version","pos":[45817,45824]},{"content":"4.5.1","pos":[45825,45830]},{"content":"Type","pos":[45835,45839]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[45840,45851]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[45856,45865]},{"content":"CD0048A","pos":[45866,45873]},{"content":"CD0048B","pos":[45886,45893]},{"pos":[45934,46021],"content":"49: ResolveAssemblyReference task now warns on dependencies with the wrong architecture","linkify":"49: ResolveAssemblyReference task now warns on dependencies with the wrong architecture","nodes":[{"content":"49: ResolveAssemblyReference task now warns on dependencies with the wrong architecture","pos":[0,87]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[46042,46049]},{"content":"The task emits a warning, MSB3270, which indicates that a reference or any of its dependencies does not match the app's architecture.","pos":[46050,46183]},{"content":"For example, this occurs if an app that was compiled with the anycpu option includes an x86 reference.","pos":[46184,46286]},{"content":"Such a scenario could result in an app failure at run time (in this case, if the app is deployed as an x64 process).","pos":[46287,46403]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[46408,46418]},{"content":"There are two areas of impact:","pos":[46419,46449]},{"content":"Recompilation generates warnings that did not appear when the app was compiled under a previous version of MSBuild.","pos":[46462,46577]},{"content":"However, because the warning identifies a possible source of runtime failure, it should be investigated and addressed.","pos":[46578,46696]},{"content":"If warnings are treated as errors, the app will fail to compile.","pos":[46709,46773]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[46778,46783]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[46784,46789]},{"content":"Version","pos":[46794,46801]},{"content":"4.5.1","pos":[46802,46807]},{"content":"Type","pos":[46812,46816]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[46817,46828]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[46833,46842]},{"content":"CD0049","pos":[46843,46849]},{"pos":[46890,46935],"content":"51: WPF TextBox defaults to undo limit of 100","linkify":"51: WPF TextBox defaults to undo limit of 100","nodes":[{"content":"51: WPF TextBox defaults to undo limit of 100","pos":[0,45]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[46956,46963]},{"content":"In .NET 4.5, the default undo limit for a WPF textbox is 100 (as opposed to being unlimited in .NET 4.0)","pos":[46964,47068]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[47073,47083]},{"content":"If an undo limit of 100 is too low, the limit can be set explicitly with the TextBox's UndoLimit property","pos":[47084,47189]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[47194,47199]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[47200,47204]},{"content":"Version","pos":[47209,47216]},{"content":"4.5","pos":[47217,47220]},{"content":"Type","pos":[47225,47229]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[47230,47237]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[47242,47255]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[47324,47333]},{"content":"CD0051","pos":[47334,47340]},{"pos":[47381,47495],"content":"55: Exceptions during unobserved processing in System.Threading.Tasks.Task no longer propagate on finalizer thread","linkify":"55: Exceptions during unobserved processing in System.Threading.Tasks.Task no longer propagate on finalizer thread","nodes":[{"content":"55: Exceptions during unobserved processing in System.Threading.Tasks.Task no longer propagate on finalizer thread","pos":[0,114]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[47516,47523]},{"content":"Because the System.Threading.Tasks.Task class represents an asynchronous operation, it catches all non-severe exceptions that occur during asynchronous processing.","pos":[47524,47687]},{"content":"In the .NET Framework 4.5, if an exception is not observed and your code never waits on the task, the exception will no longer propagate on the finalizer thread and crash the process during garbage collection.","pos":[47688,47897]},{"content":"This change enhances the reliability of applications that use the Task class to perform unobserved asynchronous processing.","pos":[47898,48021]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[48026,48036]},{"pos":[48037,48485],"content":"If an app depends on unobserved asynchronous exceptions propagating to the finalizer thread, the previous behavior can be restored by providing an appropriate handler for the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>TaskScheduler.UnobservedTaskException<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/system.threading.tasks.taskscheduler.unobservedtaskexception\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx)</ept> event, or by setting a <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>runtime configuration element<ept id=\"p2\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/jj160346%28v=vs.110%29.aspx)</ept>.","source":"If an app depends on unobserved asynchronous exceptions propagating to the finalizer thread, the previous behavior can be restored by providing an appropriate handler for the [TaskScheduler.UnobservedTaskException](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/system.threading.tasks.taskscheduler.unobservedtaskexception\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx) event, or by setting a [runtime configuration element](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/jj160346%28v=vs.110%29.aspx)."},{"content":"Scope","pos":[48490,48495]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[48496,48500]},{"content":"Version","pos":[48505,48512]},{"content":"4.5","pos":[48513,48516]},{"content":"Type","pos":[48521,48525]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[48526,48533]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[48538,48551]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[49850,49859]},{"content":"CD0055","pos":[49860,49866]},{"pos":[49907,50006],"content":"58: IAsyncResult.CompletedSynchronously property must be correct for the resulting task to complete","linkify":"58: IAsyncResult.CompletedSynchronously property must be correct for the resulting task to complete","nodes":[{"content":"58: IAsyncResult.CompletedSynchronously property must be correct for the resulting task to complete","pos":[0,99]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[50027,50034]},{"content":"When calling TaskFactory.FromAsync, the implementation of the IAsyncResult.CompletedSynchronously property must be correct for the resulting task to complete.","pos":[50035,50193]},{"content":"That is, the property must return true if, and only if, the implementation completed synchronously.","pos":[50194,50293]},{"content":"Previously, the property was not checked.","pos":[50294,50335]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[50340,50350]},{"content":"If IAsyncResult implementations correctly return true for the CompletedSynchronusly property only when a task completed synchronously, then no break will be observed.","pos":[50351,50517]},{"content":"Users should review IAsyncResult implementations they own (if any) to ensure that they correctly evaluate whether a task completed synchronously or not.","pos":[50518,50670]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[50675,50680]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[50681,50685]},{"content":"Version","pos":[50690,50697]},{"content":"4.5","pos":[50698,50701]},{"content":"Type","pos":[50706,50710]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[50711,50722]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[50727,50740]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[56600,56609]},{"content":"CD0058","pos":[56610,56616]},{"pos":[56657,56772],"content":"59: Log file name created by the ObjectContext.CreateDatabase method has changed to match SQL Server specifications","linkify":"59: Log file name created by the ObjectContext.CreateDatabase method has changed to match SQL Server specifications","nodes":[{"content":"59: Log file name created by the ObjectContext.CreateDatabase method has changed to match SQL Server specifications","pos":[0,115]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[56793,56800]},{"content":"When the CreateDatabase method is called either directly or by using Code First with the SqlClient provider and an AttachDBFilename value in the connection string, it creates a log file named filename_log.ldf instead of filename.ldf (where filename is the name of the file specified by the AttachDBFilename value).","pos":[56801,57115]},{"content":"This change improves debugging by providing a log file named according to SQL Server specifications.","pos":[57116,57216]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[57221,57231]},{"content":"If the log file name is important for an app, the app should be updated to expect the standard _log.ldf file name format.","pos":[57232,57353]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[57358,57363]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[57364,57368]},{"content":"Version","pos":[57373,57380]},{"content":"4.5","pos":[57381,57384]},{"content":"Type","pos":[57389,57393]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[57394,57401]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[57406,57419]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[57505,57514]},{"content":"CD0059","pos":[57515,57521]},{"pos":[57562,57680],"content":"60: Page.LoadComplete event no longer causes System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource control to invoke data binding","linkify":"60: Page.LoadComplete event no longer causes System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource control to invoke data binding","nodes":[{"content":"60: Page.LoadComplete event no longer causes System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource control to invoke data binding","pos":[0,118]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[57701,57708]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">`Page.LoadComplete`</ph> event no longer causes the System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource control to invoke data binding for changes to create/update/delete parameters.","pos":[57709,57881],"source":"The `Page.LoadComplete` event no longer causes the System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource control to invoke data binding for changes to create/update/delete parameters."},{"content":"This change eliminates an extraneous trip to the database, prevents the values of controls from being reset, and produces behavior that is consistent with other data controls, such as SqlDataSource and ObjectDataSource.","pos":[57882,58101]},{"content":"This change produces different behavior in the unlikely event that applications rely on invoking data binding in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Page.LoadComplete`</ph> event.","pos":[58102,58245],"source":" This change produces different behavior in the unlikely event that applications rely on invoking data binding in the `Page.LoadComplete` event."},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[58250,58260]},{"content":"If there is a need for databinding, manually invoke databind in an event that is earlier in the post-back.","pos":[58261,58367]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[58372,58377]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[58378,58382]},{"content":"Version","pos":[58387,58394]},{"content":"4.5","pos":[58395,58398]},{"content":"Type","pos":[58403,58407]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[58408,58415]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[58420,58429]},{"content":"CD0060","pos":[58430,58436]},{"pos":[58477,58544],"content":"61: WebUtility.HtmlDecode no longer decodes invalid input sequences","linkify":"61: WebUtility.HtmlDecode no longer decodes invalid input sequences","nodes":[{"content":"61: WebUtility.HtmlDecode no longer decodes invalid input sequences","pos":[0,67]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[58565,58572]},{"content":"By default, decoding methods no longer decode an invalid input sequence into an invalid UTF-16 string.","pos":[58573,58675]},{"content":"Instead, they return the original input.","pos":[58676,58716]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[58721,58731]},{"content":"The change in decoder output should matter only if you store binary data instead of UTF-16 data in strings.","pos":[58732,58839]},{"content":"To explicitly control this behavior, set the <ph id=\"ph1\">`aspnet:AllowRelaxedUnicodeDecoding`</ph> attribute of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>appSettings<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ms228154\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx)</ept> element to true to enable legacy behavior or to false to enable the current behavior.","pos":[58840,59100],"source":" To explicitly control this behavior, set the `aspnet:AllowRelaxedUnicodeDecoding` attribute of the [appSettings](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ms228154\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx) element to true to enable legacy behavior or to false to enable the current behavior."},{"content":"Scope","pos":[59105,59110]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[59111,59116]},{"content":"Version","pos":[59121,59128]},{"content":"4.5","pos":[59129,59132]},{"content":"Type","pos":[59137,59141]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[59142,59149]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[59154,59167]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[59470,59479]},{"content":"CD0061","pos":[59480,59486]},{"pos":[59527,59629],"content":"63: Apps published with ClickOnce that use a SHA-256 code-signing certificate may fail on Windows 2003","linkify":"63: Apps published with ClickOnce that use a SHA-256 code-signing certificate may fail on Windows 2003","nodes":[{"content":"63: Apps published with ClickOnce that use a SHA-256 code-signing certificate may fail on Windows 2003","pos":[0,102]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[59650,59657]},{"content":"The executable is signed with SHA256.","pos":[59658,59695]},{"content":"Previously, it was signed with SHA1 regardless of whether the code-signing certificate was SHA-1 or SHA-256.","pos":[59696,59804]},{"content":"This applies to:","pos":[59805,59821]},{"content":"All applications built with Visual Studio 2012 or later.","pos":[59834,59890]},{"content":"Applications built with Visual Studio 2010 or earlier on systems with the .NET Framework 4.5 present.","pos":[59903,60004]},{"content":"In addition, if the .NET Framework 4.5 or later is present, the ClickOnce manifest is also signed with SHA-256 for SHA-256 certificates regardless of the .NET Framework version against which it was compiled.","pos":[60017,60224]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[60229,60239]},{"content":"The change in signing the ClickOnce executable affects only Windows Server 2003 systems; they require that KB 938397 be installed.","pos":[60240,60370]},{"content":"The change in signing the manifest with SHA-256 even when an app targets the .NET Framework 4.0 or earlier versions introduces a runtime dependency on the .NET Framework 4.5 or a later version.","pos":[60383,60576]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[60581,60586]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[60587,60591]},{"content":"Version","pos":[60596,60603]},{"content":"4.5-4.6","pos":[60604,60611]},{"content":"Type","pos":[60616,60620]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[60621,60632]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[60637,60646]},{"content":"CD0063","pos":[60647,60653]},{"pos":[60694,60772],"content":"68: DbParameter.Precision and DbParameter.Scale are now public virtual members","linkify":"68: DbParameter.Precision and DbParameter.Scale are now public virtual members","nodes":[{"content":"68: DbParameter.Precision and DbParameter.Scale are now public virtual members","pos":[0,78]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[60793,60800]},{"content":"DbParameter.Precision and DbParameter.Scale are implemented as public virtual properties.","pos":[60801,60890]},{"content":"They replace the corresponding explicit interface implementations, DbParameter.IDbDataParameter.Precision and DbParameter.IDbDataParameter.Scale.","pos":[60891,61036]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[61041,61051]},{"content":"When re-building an ADO.NET database provider, these differences will require the 'override' keyword to be applied to the Precision and Scale properties.","pos":[61052,61205]},{"content":"This is only needed when re-building the components; exisiting binaries will continue to work.","pos":[61206,61300]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[61305,61310]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[61311,61316]},{"content":"Version","pos":[61321,61328]},{"content":"4.5.1","pos":[61329,61334]},{"content":"Type","pos":[61339,61343]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[61344,61355]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[61360,61373]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[61532,61541]},{"content":"CD0068","pos":[61542,61548]},{"pos":[61589,61639],"content":"73: DataObject.GetData now retrieves data as UTF-8","linkify":"73: DataObject.GetData now retrieves data as UTF-8","nodes":[{"content":"73: DataObject.GetData now retrieves data as UTF-8","pos":[0,50]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[61660,61667]},{"content":"For apps that target the .NET Framework 4 or that run on the .NET Framework 4.5.1 or earlier versions, DataObject.GetData retrieves HTML-formatted data as an ASCII string.","pos":[61668,61839]},{"content":"As a result, non-ASCII characters (characters whose ASCII codes are greater than 0x7F) are represented by two random characters.","pos":[61840,61968]},{"content":"For apps that target the .NET Framework 4.5 or later and run on the .NET Framework 4.5.2, <ph id=\"ph1\">`DataObject.GetData`</ph> retrieves HTML-formatted data as UTF-8, which represents characters greater than 0x7F correctly.","pos":[61981,62188],"source":" For apps that target the .NET Framework 4.5 or later and run on the .NET Framework 4.5.2, `DataObject.GetData` retrieves HTML-formatted data as UTF-8, which represents characters greater than 0x7F correctly."},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[62193,62203]},{"content":"If you implemented a workaround for the encoding problem with HTML-formatted strings (for example, by explicitly encoding the HTML string retrieved from the Clipboard by passing it to the UTF8Encoding.GetString method) and you're retargeting your app from version 4 to 4.5, that workaround should be removed.","pos":[62204,62512]},{"content":"If the old behavior is needed for some reason, the app can target the .NET Framework 4.0 to get that behavior.","pos":[62525,62635]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[62640,62645]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[62646,62650]},{"content":"Version","pos":[62655,62662]},{"content":"4.5.2","pos":[62663,62668]},{"content":"Type","pos":[62673,62677]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[62678,62689]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[62694,62707]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[63006,63015]},{"content":"CD0073","pos":[63016,63022]},{"pos":[63063,63147],"content":"75: TargetFrameworkName for default app domain no longer defaults to null if not set","linkify":"75: TargetFrameworkName for default app domain no longer defaults to null if not set","nodes":[{"content":"75: TargetFrameworkName for default app domain no longer defaults to null if not set","pos":[0,84]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[63168,63175]},{"content":"The TargetFrameworkName was previously null in the default app domain, unless it was explicitly set.","pos":[63176,63276]},{"content":"Beginning in 4.6, the TargetFrameworkName property for the default app domain will have a default value derived from the TargetFrameworkAttribute (if one is present).","pos":[63277,63443]},{"content":"Non-default app domains will continue to inherit their TargetFrameworkName from the default app domain (which will not default to null in 4.6) unless it is explicitly overridden.","pos":[63444,63622]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[63627,63637]},{"content":"Code should be updated to not depend on <ph id=\"ph1\">`AppDomainSetup.TargetFrameworkName`</ph> defaulting to null.","pos":[63638,63734],"source":"Code should be updated to not depend on `AppDomainSetup.TargetFrameworkName` defaulting to null."},{"content":"If it is required that this property continue to evaluate to null, it can be explicitly set to that value.","pos":[63735,63841]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[63846,63851]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[63852,63856]},{"content":"Version","pos":[63861,63868]},{"content":"4.6","pos":[63869,63872]},{"content":"Type","pos":[63877,63881]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[63882,63889]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[63894,63907]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[63986,63995]},{"content":"CD0075B","pos":[63996,64003]},{"content":"CD0075A","pos":[64016,64023]},{"pos":[64064,64158],"content":"76: X509Certificate2.ToString(bool) does not throw now when .NET cannot handle the certificate","linkify":"76: X509Certificate2.ToString(bool) does not throw now when .NET cannot handle the certificate","nodes":[{"content":"76: X509Certificate2.ToString(bool) does not throw now when .NET cannot handle the certificate","pos":[0,94]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[64179,64186]},{"content":"Previously, this method would throw if 'true' was passed for the verbose parameter and there were certificates installed that weren't supported by the .Net Framework.","pos":[64187,64353]},{"content":"Now, the method will succeed and return a valid string that omits the inaccessible portions of the certifiate.","pos":[64354,64464]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[64469,64479]},{"content":"Any code depending on X509Certificate2.ToString(bool) should be updated to expect that the returned string may exclude some certificate data (such as public key, private key, and extensions) in some cases in which the API would have previously thrown.","pos":[64480,64731]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[64736,64741]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[64742,64746]},{"content":"Version","pos":[64751,64758]},{"content":"4.6","pos":[64759,64762]},{"content":"Type","pos":[64767,64771]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[64772,64779]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[64784,64797]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[64926,64935]},{"content":"CD0076","pos":[64936,64942]},{"pos":[64983,65078],"content":"77: Reflection objects can no longer be passed from managed code to out-of-process DCOM clients","linkify":"77: Reflection objects can no longer be passed from managed code to out-of-process DCOM clients","nodes":[{"content":"77: Reflection objects can no longer be passed from managed code to out-of-process DCOM clients","pos":[0,95]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[65099,65106]},{"content":"Reflection objects can no longer be passed from managed code to out-of-process DCOM clients.","pos":[65107,65199]},{"content":"The following types are affected:","pos":[65200,65233]},{"content":"Assembly","pos":[65246,65254]},{"content":"MemberInfo (and its derived types, including FieldInfo, MethodInfo, Type, and TypeInfo)","pos":[65267,65354]},{"content":"MethodBody","pos":[65367,65377]},{"content":"Module","pos":[65390,65396]},{"content":"ParameterInfo.","pos":[65409,65423]},{"content":"Calls to <ph id=\"ph1\">`IMarshal`</ph> for the object return <ph id=\"ph2\">`E_NOINTERFACE`</ph>.","pos":[65436,65494],"source":" Calls to `IMarshal` for the object return `E_NOINTERFACE`."},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[65499,65509]},{"content":"Update marshaling code to work with non-reflection objects","pos":[65510,65568]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[65573,65578]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[65579,65584]},{"content":"Version","pos":[65589,65596]},{"content":"4.6","pos":[65597,65600]},{"content":"Type","pos":[65605,65609]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[65610,65617]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[65622,65631]},{"content":"CD0077","pos":[65632,65638]},{"pos":[65679,65745],"content":"78: ContentDisposition DateTimes returns slightly different string","linkify":"78: ContentDisposition DateTimes returns slightly different string","nodes":[{"content":"78: ContentDisposition DateTimes returns slightly different string","pos":[0,66]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[65766,65773]},{"content":"String representations of ContentDispositions have been updated, beginning in 4.6, to always represent the hour component of a DateTime with two digits.","pos":[65774,65926]},{"content":"This is to comply with <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>RFC822<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc0822.txt)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>RFC2822<ept id=\"p2\">](http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2822.txt)</ept>.","pos":[65927,66047],"source":" This is to comply with [RFC822](http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc0822.txt) and [RFC2822](http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2822.txt)."},{"content":"This causes <ph id=\"ph1\">`ContentDisposition.ToString`</ph> to return a slightly different string in 4.6 in scenarios where one of the disposition's time elements was before 10:00 AM.","pos":[66048,66213],"source":" This causes `ContentDisposition.ToString` to return a slightly different string in 4.6 in scenarios where one of the disposition's time elements was before 10:00 AM."},{"content":"Note that ContentDispositions are sometimes serialized via converting them to strings, so any ContentDisposition ToString operations, serialization, or GetHashCode calls should be reviewed.","pos":[66214,66403]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[66408,66418]},{"content":"Do not expect that string representations of ContentDispositions from different .NET Framework versions will correctly compare to one another.","pos":[66419,66561]},{"content":"Convert the strings back to ContentDispositions, if possible, before conducting a comparison.","pos":[66562,66655]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[66660,66665]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[66666,66671]},{"content":"Version","pos":[66676,66683]},{"content":"4.6","pos":[66684,66687]},{"content":"Type","pos":[66692,66696]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[66697,66704]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[66709,66722]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[66894,66903]},{"content":"CD0078","pos":[66904,66910]},{"pos":[66951,67007],"content":"82: WorkflowDesigner.Load doesn't remove symbol property","linkify":"82: WorkflowDesigner.Load doesn't remove symbol property","nodes":[{"content":"82: WorkflowDesigner.Load doesn't remove symbol property","pos":[0,56]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[67028,67035]},{"content":"When targeting the .NET Framework 4.5 in the workflow designer, and loading a re-hosted 3.5 workflow with the WorkflowDesigner.Load() method, a XamlDuplicateMemberException is thrown while saving the workflow.","pos":[67036,67245]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[67250,67260]},{"content":"This bug only manifests when targeting .NET Framework 4.5 in the workflow designer, so it can be worked around by setting the <ph id=\"ph1\">`WorkflowDesigner.Context.Services.GetService&lt;DesignerConfigurationService&gt;().TargetFrameworkName`</ph> to the 4.0 .NET Framework.","pos":[67261,67512],"source":"This bug only manifests when targeting .NET Framework 4.5 in the workflow designer, so it can be worked around by setting the `WorkflowDesigner.Context.Services.GetService<DesignerConfigurationService>().TargetFrameworkName` to the 4.0 .NET Framework."},{"content":"Alternatively, the issue may be avoided by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>WorkflowContext.Load(string)<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee425926\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx)</ept> method to load the workflow, instead of <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>WorkflowDesigner.Load()<ept id=\"p2\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee403482\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx)</ept>.","pos":[67525,67799],"source":" Alternatively, the issue may be avoided by using the [WorkflowContext.Load(string)](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee425926\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx) method to load the workflow, instead of [WorkflowDesigner.Load()](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee403482\\(v=vs.110\\).aspx)."},{"content":"Scope","pos":[67804,67809]},{"content":"Major","pos":[67810,67815]},{"content":"Version","pos":[67820,67827]},{"content":"4.5-4.5.2","pos":[67828,67837]},{"content":"Type","pos":[67842,67846]},{"content":"Retargeting","pos":[67847,67858]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[67863,67876]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[67966,67975]},{"content":"CD0082","pos":[67976,67982]},{"pos":[68023,68104],"content":"83: SqlConnection.Open fails on Windows 7 with non-IFS Winsock BSP or LSP present","linkify":"83: SqlConnection.Open fails on Windows 7 with non-IFS Winsock BSP or LSP present","nodes":[{"content":"83: SqlConnection.Open fails on Windows 7 with non-IFS Winsock BSP or LSP present","pos":[0,81]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[68125,68132]},{"content":"SqlConneciton.Open and OpenAsync fail in the .NET Framework 4.5 if running on a Windows 7 machine with a non-IFS Winsock BSP or LSP are present on the computer.","pos":[68133,68293]},{"content":"To determine whether a non-IFS BSP or LSP is installed, use the <ph id=\"ph1\">`netsh WinSock Show Catalog`</ph> command, and examine every <ph id=\"ph2\">`Winsock Catalog Provider Entry`</ph> item that is returned.","pos":[68306,68481],"source":" To determine whether a non-IFS BSP or LSP is installed, use the `netsh WinSock Show Catalog` command, and examine every `Winsock Catalog Provider Entry` item that is returned."},{"content":"If the Service Flags value has the <ph id=\"ph1\">`0x20000`</ph> bit set, the provider uses IFS handles and will work correctly.","pos":[68482,68590],"source":" If the Service Flags value has the `0x20000` bit set, the provider uses IFS handles and will work correctly."},{"content":"If the <ph id=\"ph1\">`0x20000`</ph> bit is clear (not set), it is a non-IFS BSP or LSP.","pos":[68591,68659],"source":" If the `0x20000` bit is clear (not set), it is a non-IFS BSP or LSP."},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[68664,68674]},{"content":"This bug has been fixed in the .NET Framework 4.5.2, so it can be avoided by upgrading the .NET Framework.","pos":[68675,68781]},{"content":"Alternatively, it can be avoided by removing any installed non-IFS Winsock LSPs.","pos":[68782,68862]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[68867,68872]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[68873,68878]},{"content":"Version","pos":[68883,68890]},{"content":"4.5-4.5.2","pos":[68891,68900]},{"content":"Type","pos":[68905,68909]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[68910,68917]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[68922,68935]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[69143,69152]},{"content":"CD0083","pos":[69153,69159]},{"pos":[69200,69266],"content":"84: ICommand.CanExecuteChanged event behaviour changed in .NET 4.5","linkify":"84: ICommand.CanExecuteChanged event behaviour changed in .NET 4.5","nodes":[{"content":"84: ICommand.CanExecuteChanged event behaviour changed in .NET 4.5","pos":[0,66]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[69287,69294]},{"content":"In the .NET Framework 4.5, a CanExecuteChangedEvent was ignored unless the sender of the event was the same object as the object that raised the event.","pos":[69295,69446]},{"content":"This bug was fixed in .NET Framework 4.5 servcing updates.","pos":[69447,69505]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[69510,69520]},{"content":"This bug has been fixed in the .NET Framework 4.5 servicing releases, so it can be avoided by making sure that the .NET Framework is up-to-date or by upgrading to .NET Framework 4.5.1.","pos":[69521,69705]},{"content":"Alternatively, application code using ICommand can be modified to make sure that the sender when raising a CanExecuteChanged command is the same as the object raising the event.","pos":[69706,69883]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[69888,69893]},{"content":"Minor","pos":[69894,69899]},{"content":"Version","pos":[69904,69911]},{"content":"4.5-4.5","pos":[69912,69919]},{"content":"Type","pos":[69924,69928]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[69929,69936]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[69941,69954]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[70039,70048]},{"content":"CD0084","pos":[70049,70055]},{"pos":[70096,70172],"content":"85: Some .NET APIs cause first chance (handled) EntryPointNotFoundExceptions","linkify":"85: Some .NET APIs cause first chance (handled) EntryPointNotFoundExceptions","nodes":[{"content":"85: Some .NET APIs cause first chance (handled) EntryPointNotFoundExceptions","pos":[0,76]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[70193,70200]},{"content":"In the .NET Framework 4.5, a small number of .NET methods began throwing first chance EntryPointNotFoundExceptions.","pos":[70201,70316]},{"content":"These exceptions were handled within the .Net Framework, but could break test automation that did not expect the first chance exceptions.","pos":[70317,70454]},{"content":"These same APIs break some ApiVerifier scenarios when HighVersionLie is enabled.","pos":[70455,70535]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[70540,70550]},{"content":"This bug can be avoided by upgrading to .NET Framework 4.5.1.","pos":[70551,70612]},{"content":"Alternatively, test automation can be updated to not break on first-chance EntryPointNotFoundExceptions.","pos":[70613,70717]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[70722,70727]},{"content":"Edge","pos":[70728,70732]},{"content":"Version","pos":[70737,70744]},{"content":"4.5-4.5.1","pos":[70745,70754]},{"content":"Type","pos":[70759,70763]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[70764,70771]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[70776,70789]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[71376,71385]},{"content":"CD0085","pos":[71386,71392]},{"pos":[71433,71525],"content":"86: Scrolling a WPF TreeView or grouped ListBox in a VirtualizingStackPanel can cause a hang","linkify":"86: Scrolling a WPF TreeView or grouped ListBox in a VirtualizingStackPanel can cause a hang","nodes":[{"content":"86: Scrolling a WPF TreeView or grouped ListBox in a VirtualizingStackPanel can cause a hang","pos":[0,92]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[71546,71553]},{"content":"In the .NET Framework v4.5, scrolling a WPF TreeView in a virtualized stack panel can cause hangs if there are margins in the viewport (between the items in the TreeView, for example, or on an ItemsPresenter element).","pos":[71554,71771]},{"content":"Additionally, in some cases, different sized items in the view can cause instability even if there are no margins.","pos":[71772,71886]},{"content":"Suggestion","pos":[71891,71901]},{"content":"This bug can be avoided by upgrading to .NET Framework 4.5.1.","pos":[71902,71963]},{"content":"Alternatively, margins can be removed from view collections (like TreeViews) within virtualized stack panels if all contained items are the same size.","pos":[71964,72114]},{"content":"Scope","pos":[72119,72124]},{"content":"Major","pos":[72125,72130]},{"content":"Version","pos":[72135,72142]},{"content":"4.5-4.5.1","pos":[72143,72152]},{"content":"Type","pos":[72157,72161]},{"content":"Runtime","pos":[72162,72169]},{"content":"Affected APIs","pos":[72174,72187]},{"content":"Analyzers","pos":[72338,72347]},{"content":"CD0086","pos":[72348,72354]},{"content":"CD0086","pos":[72367,72373]},{"pos":[72414,72499],"content":"89: Type.IsAssignableFrom returns wrong result for generic variables with constraints","linkify":"89: Type.IsAssignableFrom returns wrong result for generic variables with constraints","nodes":[{"content":"89: Type.IsAssignableFrom returns wrong result for generic variables with constraints","pos":[0,85]}]},{"content":"Details","pos":[72520,72527]},{"pos":[72528,72662],"content":"In the .NET 